  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently there is no out-of-the-box way to include AWSRequestId into log records.\r\nThere is com.amazonaws:aws-lambda-java-log4j2 library which does that, but it's is not very quarkus-friendly (at least last time I've tried it).\r\nOf course developer could do MDC.put(\"AWSRequestId\", context.getAwsRequestId()) in RequestHandler, but would be nice to have this working without additional code. And also it's not very clear how to do this for quarkus-amazon-lambda-http + quarkus-resteasy. \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
